news.title: Bengaluru civic body seals 830 commercial properties
news.para: According to BBMP’s Special Commissioner (Revenue) Munish Moudgil, the BBMP has sealed properties across its eight zones as part of its action against tax defaulters.

news.title: No construction here: Warning boards soon on New Noida land
news.para: ​During a meeting on Thursday, CEO Lokesh M, along with Bulandshahr district magistrate CP Singh and officials from the Noida and Bulandshahr development authorities, asked for the installation of boards that warned villagers of demolition of unauthorised structures.

news.title: Macrotech Developers acquires 20-acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: Out of the total, nearly 20 acre land was acquired in Bengaluru, the company has outright purchased some portion of land, while entering into joint development agreement with the landowner for the remaining part, sources said.

news.title: Lucknow development body earns Rs 450 crore in e-auction
news.para: The auction, held on Jan 7, followed registration from Nov 11, 2024, to Jan 3, and saw 59 out of 325 properties sold.

news.title: Projects under Ludhiana smart city mission may miss more deadlines
news.para: ​Despite the long time they have already taken, projects, including the 24x7 surface water supply project for selected areas, bioremediation of legacy waste (first phase), and establishment of construction and demolition waste plants, are still pending.

news.title: Property allottees pay heavy price for Chandigarh estate office's glitch
news.para: The incorrect tagging of properties during the digitalisation of records has created substantial challenges, with owners spending years attempting to correct these errors.

news.title: NCLAT gives go-ahead for Indiabulls Real Estate-Embassy Group merger
news.para: ​"We set aside the impugned order of NCLT, Chandigarh and allow the prayer to sanction the scheme of amalgamation between the appellants (Indiabulls Real Estate, Embassy one & NAM Estates)," said a two-member NCLAT bench.

news.title: Regularisation plea can be entertained only if structure is irregular, not illegal: HC
news.para: The high court held that an application under the Regularisation Act can be entertained only if the structure is an irregular structure and not an illegal structure, and it was in existence and constructed as an irregular structure prior to Feb 28, 2014.

news.title: Signature Global acquires 16.12 acres land in Gurugram
news.para: Signature Global had reported pre-sales of Rs 86.7 billion during the first nine months of FY25, recording 178 per cent growth year-on-year.

news.title: Oberoi Realty to redevelop 10,300 sq meter land in Mumbai
news.para: The company expects to be entitled to a free sale component of around 3.2 lakh sq ft from the development and redevelopment of the said land.

news.title: Supertech Township Projects lender rejects settlement proposal, NCLAT to decide on insolvency
news.para: Counsel representing Ram Kishore Arora, the suspended director of the realty firm informed NCLAT on Thursday about the rejection of the settlement proposal.

news.title: Sunteck Realty sale bookings up 40% to Rs 635 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing late Friday, Sunteck Realty said the company's sale bookings or pre-sales in the year-ago period was Rs 455 crore.

news.title: China's Evergrande Group ordered to repay its property unit $1.8 billion worth deposit pledges
news.para: Evergrande Property began legal proceedings against its indebted parent early last year for using its deposits as collateral for pledge guarantees.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 949 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: The enforcement drive targeted several commercial establishments, including properties in Haridarshan Estate (Ramol), Pujan Commercial Complex (Nikol), Parishikhar Estate (Ramol), and Palm Arcade (Nikol).

news.title: Redsun Properties to miss $350 million bond payment due next week
news.para: A prolonged property market slump in China over the last three years has been weighing on developers' ability to repay debt.

news.title: China's Shimao Group receives liquidation petition
news.para: This is the second case of such petitions against Chinese property developers in the last two days. On Thursday, a petition was filed against embattled property developer Sunac China to wind down by asset manager China Cinda Asset Management.

news.title: Kerala HC rules against fee on large buildings in converted lands
news.para: Justice C P Mohamed Nias issued the ruling on a batch of petitions challenging the provision imposing the fee under Note 1 to Rule 12(9) of the Kerala Conservation of Paddy Land and Wetland Rules (the Rules), framed under the Act.

news.title: Jaipur development body removes encroachments from 600 bighas of govt land
news.para: Officials mentioned that in the recent Govind Vihar scheme, plots are being made available after JDA removed encroachment from 250 bighas of land worth Rs 1,300 crore in Zone-10 in Nov 2024.

news.title: Meeting to be held next week on property tax and issues of merged areas: Maharashtra minister
news.para: The Parvati Member of Legislative Assembly (MLA) was speaking to the media after a meeting with civic officials at the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) headquarters to discuss ongoing civic projects in the city.

news.title: Madras HC forms SIT to probe illegal sand mining in Kovai
news.para: A special division bench appointed G Nagajothi, superintendent of police, State Crime Records Bureau, Chennai, and F Shashank Sai, SP, Organised Crime Intelligence Unit as members of SIT.
